{"id":187706,"date":"2023-08-16T09:23:12","date_gmt":"2023-08-16T03:53:12","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=187706"},"modified":"2023-09-26T08:59:06","modified_gmt":"2023-09-26T03:29:06","slug":"aroon-purie","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/","title":{"rendered":"Aroon Purie (Journalist) Wiki, Age, Wife, Family, Children, Biography, Facts &amp; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-187772\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie.jpg\" alt=\"Aroon Purie\" width=\"583\" height=\"428\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie.jpg 742w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-300x220.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 583px) 100vw, 583px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Aroon Purie is an Indian media tycoon who is the founder-publisher and editor-in-chief of India Today magazine. He used to lead the India Today Group. He is the managing director of Thomson Press (India) Limited and chairman of TV Today. He is the recipient of the Padma Bhushan Award. Aroon Purie is the former editor-in-chief of Reader&#8217;s Digest India. In 2017, he gave control of the India Today Group to his daughter, Kalli Purie.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce3fc29c64\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/label><input type=\"checkbox\"  id=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce3fc29c64\"  aria-label=\"Toggle\" \/><nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/#WikiBiography\" title=\"Wiki\/Biography\">Wiki\/Biography<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/#Physical_Appearance\" title=\"Physical Appearance\">Physical Appearance<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/#Family\" title=\"Family\">Family<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/#Parents_Siblings\" title=\"Parents &amp; Siblings\">Parents &amp; Siblings<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/#Wife_Children\" title=\"Wife &amp; Children\">Wife &amp; Children<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/#Career\" title=\"Career\">Career<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/#India_Today_Magazine\" title=\"India Today Magazine\">India Today Magazine<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/#Other_Associations\" title=\"Other Associations\">Other Associations<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/#Controversies\" title=\"Controversies\">Controversies<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/#Defamation_Case_Against_India_Today\" title=\"Defamation Case Against India Today\">Defamation Case Against India Today<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/#Plagiarism\" title=\"Plagiarism\">Plagiarism<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/#Awards_Honours_Achievements\" title=\"Awards, Honours, Achievements\">Awards, Honours, Achievements<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-13\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/aroon-purie\/#FactsTrivia\" title=\"Facts\/Trivia\">Facts\/Trivia<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"WikiBiography\"><\/span>Wiki\/Biography<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Aroon Purie was born in 1944 (<strong>age 74 years; as of 2023<\/strong>) in Lahore, Punjab province, British India. He has completed his school education at The Doon School, Dehradun, Uttarakhand. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_187706_1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_187706_1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.telegraphindia.com\/india\/dame-dilemma-for-doon-president-s-co-ed-suggestion-evokes-mixed-reaction\/cid\/473014\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Telegraph Online<\/a><\/span><\/span> In 1965, he completed a bachelor&#8217;s degree in economics from the London School of Economics. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_187706_1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_187706_1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.indiatoday.in\/india\/story\/india-today-group-chairman-aroon-purie-honoured-with-ablf-lifetime-achievement-award-1926185-2022-03-16\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">India Today<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Physical_Appearance\"><\/span>Physical Appearance<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><strong>Hair Colour: <\/strong>Salt and Pepper<\/p>\n<p><strong>Eye Colour: <\/strong>Black<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-Picture.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-187773\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-Picture.jpg\" alt=\"Aroon Purie\" width=\"421\" height=\"346\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-Picture.jpg 547w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-Picture-300x247.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 421px) 100vw, 421px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Family\"><\/span>Family<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Aroon Purie belongs to a Hindu family, and according to him, his father was a follower of the Arya Samaj community. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_187706_1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[3]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_187706_1_3\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.indiatoday.in\/magazine\/editor-s-note\/story\/20180129-from-the-editor-in-chief-hindu-vs-hindutva-aroon-purie-1148708-2018-01-19\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">India Today<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Parents_Siblings\"><\/span><strong>Parents &amp; Siblings<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>His father, Vidya Vilas Purie, was the founder of the India Today Group. Vidya Vilas Purie was a film financer and the owner of Thompson Press. His sister, Madhu Trehan, is an Indian journalist.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_187779\" style=\"width: 370px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Puries-aunt-Madhu-Trehan-1.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-187779\" class=\" wp-image-187779\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Puries-aunt-Madhu-Trehan-1.jpg\" alt=\"Aroon Purie's sister, Madhu Trehan\" width=\"360\" height=\"381\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Puries-aunt-Madhu-Trehan-1.jpg 413w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Puries-aunt-Madhu-Trehan-1-284x300.jpg 284w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-187779\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aroon Purie&#8217;s sister, Madhu Trehan<\/p><\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Wife_Children\"><\/span><strong>Wife &amp; Children<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Aroon Purie is married to Rekha Purie.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_187761\" style=\"width: 520px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Puries-parents-1.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-187761\" class=\" wp-image-187761\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Puries-parents-1.jpg\" alt=\"Aroon Purie with his wife\" width=\"510\" height=\"365\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Puries-parents-1.jpg 676w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Puries-parents-1-300x214.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 510px) 100vw, 510px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-187761\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aroon Purie with his wife<\/p><\/div>\n<p>The couple has a son and two daughters. His son&#8217;s name is Ankoor Purie, and his daughters&#8217; names are Kalli Purie and <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/koel-purie\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Koel Purie<\/a>.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_187593\" style=\"width: 335px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Ankoor-Purie.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-187593\" class=\" wp-image-187593\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Ankoor-Purie.jpg\" alt=\"A picture of Ankoor Purie, Koel Purie's brother\" width=\"325\" height=\"382\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Ankoor-Purie.jpg 292w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Ankoor-Purie-255x300.jpg 255w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 325px) 100vw, 325px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-187593\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A picture of Ankoor Purie, Koel Purie&#8217;s brother<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_187594\" style=\"width: 338px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Puries-sister-Kalli-Puri.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-187594\" class=\" wp-image-187594\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Puries-sister-Kalli-Puri.jpg\" alt=\"Aroon Purie's daughter, Kalli Puri\" width=\"328\" height=\"303\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Puries-sister-Kalli-Puri.jpg 490w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Puries-sister-Kalli-Puri-300x277.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 328px) 100vw, 328px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-187594\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aroon Purie&#8217;s daughter, Kalli Puri<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_187581\" style=\"width: 337px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Purie-Picture.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-187581\" class=\" wp-image-187581\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Purie-Picture.jpg\" alt=\"A picture of Koel Purie\" width=\"327\" height=\"295\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Purie-Picture.jpg 727w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Koel-Purie-Picture-300x270.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 327px) 100vw, 327px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-187581\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A picture of Koel Purie<\/p><\/div>\n<p>Ankoor Purie and Kalli Purie are into journalism while <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/koel-purie\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Koel Purie<\/a> is an Indian actress.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career\"><\/span>Career<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>In 1970, Aroon Purie began working as a production controller at Thomson Press, a commercial printer and allied services company. Even though he later gave control of Thomson Press to his son Ankoor Purie, he still guides it. Thomson Press has five branches in different parts of India. In 1975, he started the India Today Group, which has a magazine with the same name. This group is known for its varied media approaches all across India including 32 magazines, 7 radio stations, 4 television channels, 1 newspaper, lots of websites and apps, a famous music label, and a book publishing part.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_187899\" style=\"width: 313px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/A-young-Aroon-Purie.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-187899\" class=\"size-full wp-image-187899\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/A-young-Aroon-Purie.jpg\" alt=\"A young Aroon Purie\" width=\"303\" height=\"370\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/A-young-Aroon-Purie.jpg 303w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/A-young-Aroon-Purie-246x300.jpg 246w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 303px) 100vw, 303px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-187899\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A young Aroon Purie<\/p><\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"India_Today_Magazine\"><\/span><strong>India Today Magazine<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Vidya Vilas Purie, the father of Aroon Purie, started a magazine called India Today in 1975. Aroon&#8217;s sister Madhu Trehan was appointed as the editor, and Aroon Purie was designated as in charge of the magazine on its launch.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_187901\" style=\"width: 480px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Dilip-Bobb-Aroon-Purie-Madhu-Trehan-Shirley-Joshua-and-Mohini-Bhullar-at-the-Taj-Hotel-in-New-Delhi.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-187901\" class=\" wp-image-187901\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Dilip-Bobb-Aroon-Purie-Madhu-Trehan-Shirley-Joshua-and-Mohini-Bhullar-at-the-Taj-Hotel-in-New-Delhi.jpg\" alt=\"An old picture of Dilip Bobb, Aroon Purie, Madhu Trehan, Shirley Joshua, and Mohini Bhullar at the Taj Hotel in New Delhi\" width=\"470\" height=\"342\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Dilip-Bobb-Aroon-Purie-Madhu-Trehan-Shirley-Joshua-and-Mohini-Bhullar-at-the-Taj-Hotel-in-New-Delhi.jpg 623w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Dilip-Bobb-Aroon-Purie-Madhu-Trehan-Shirley-Joshua-and-Mohini-Bhullar-at-the-Taj-Hotel-in-New-Delhi-300x218.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 470px) 100vw, 470px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-187901\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">An old picture of Dilip Bobb, Aroon Purie, Madhu Trehan, Shirley Joshua, and Mohini Bhullar at the Taj Hotel in New Delhi<\/p><\/div>\n<p>They launched the magazine when the then Prime Minister of India, <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/indira-gandhi\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Indira Gandhi<\/a>, declared an Emergency. Aroon Purie wanted to share information about India with people who were living in other countries through this magazine. The magazine started publishing in five languages, and lots of people in India read it. Reportedly, after its launch, it became the most popular magazine for more than ten years, with over 11 million readers. Later, Aroon Purie set the style of journalism for the Hindi news channel named Aaj Tak and the English news channel Headlines Today.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_187898\" style=\"width: 358px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/The-cover-of-the-India-Today-magazine.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-187898\" class=\" wp-image-187898\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/The-cover-of-the-India-Today-magazine.jpg\" alt=\"The cover of the India Today magazine\" width=\"348\" height=\"495\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/The-cover-of-the-India-Today-magazine.jpg 362w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/The-cover-of-the-India-Today-magazine-211x300.jpg 211w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 348px) 100vw, 348px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-187898\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The cover of the India Today magazine<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_187900\" style=\"width: 507px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-interviewing-Morarji-Desai-in-New-Delhi-in-August-1979.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-187900\" class=\" wp-image-187900\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-interviewing-Morarji-Desai-in-New-Delhi-in-August-1979.jpg\" alt=\"Aroon Purie interviewing Morarji Desai in New Delhi in August 1979\" width=\"497\" height=\"340\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-interviewing-Morarji-Desai-in-New-Delhi-in-August-1979.jpg 737w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-interviewing-Morarji-Desai-in-New-Delhi-in-August-1979-300x206.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 497px) 100vw, 497px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-187900\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aroon Purie interviewing Morarji Desai in New Delhi in August 1979<\/p><\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Other_Associations\"><\/span><strong>Other Associations<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Aroon Purie is part of many groups like the Council of Management at the Audit Bureau of Circulations, where he served as a Chairman from 2000 to 2001. He is on the Executive Committee of The Editors&#8217; Guild of India, and he&#8217;s part of the Council of Management at the All India Management Association as a special invitee. He served as the Chairman of the CII National Committee on Media from 2001 to 2002. In 2009, Aroon Purie was appointed as the chairman of FIPP (Federation of International Periodicals and Publications). Aroon Purie has been on the board of the Global Editors Network since it started in April 2011.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Controversies\"><\/span>Controversies<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Defamation_Case_Against_India_Today\"><\/span><strong>Defamation Case Against India Today<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Aroon Purie attracted controversy when a legal case was filed against him in April 2007 after a report titled &#8220;Mission Misconduct&#8221; was published in India Today magazine. This report talked about three Indian officials in the UK who were quickly brought back due to serious accusations of sexual misconduct, corruption in issuing visas, and selling Indian passports to illegal immigrants. The Supreme Court decided to cancel the case this case against Aroon Purie in October 2022. However, even though Chief Justice U.U. Lalit, Justice Ravindra Bhat, and Justice Bela M Trivedi dismissed the case against Purie; they did not provide relief to the writer of the news article. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_187706_1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[4]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_187706_1_4\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.newslaundry.com\/2022\/10\/31\/supreme-court-quashes-defamation-case-against-india-todays-aroon-purie#:~:text=The%20case%20pertains%20to%20a%202007%20report%20in%20the%20magazine.&amp;text=The%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20quashed,in%20the%20magazine%20in%202007\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">News Laundry<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Plagiarism\"><\/span><strong>Plagiarism<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>In 2010, CounterMedia discovered that the first two paragraphs of a 400-word article written by Purie on 18 October 2010 about the South Indian actor <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/rajinikanth\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Rajinikanth<\/a> were the same as the first 250 words in an article published by Grady Hendrix on 27 September 2010 in an online magazine titled Slate in the United States. Later, Purie apologised for the error and explained that it happened because he was tired from travelling. He mentioned that a few sentences from another article were sent to him. In reply, Hendrix wrote in Slate that the apology about jet lag was not meant to be taken seriously; it was more like a way to brush off the issue with a playful &#8220;Oops, I&#8217;m tired!&#8221; gesture. Hendrix also noted that he thought this resolved the matter well. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_187706_1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[5]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_187706_1_5\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/slate.com\/culture\/2010\/10\/my-slatearticle-on-rajinikanth-was-plagiarized-by-india-today.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Slate<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Awards_Honours_Achievements\"><\/span>Awards, Honours, Achievements<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>In 1988, Aroon Purie was honoured with a B.D. Goenka award for his excellence in Journalism.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In 1990, Aroon Purie earned the &#8220;Journalist of the Year&#8221; award by the Indian Federation of Small and Medium Newspapers.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In 1993-1994, he won the G.K. Reddy Memorial Award for Outstanding Contribution to Journalism.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2001, he was honoured with the Padma Bhushan, India\u2019s third highest civilian award presented by the Government of India.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_187903\" style=\"width: 312px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-being-awarded-Padma-Bhushan-Award-by-K.-R.-Narayanan-in-2001.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-187903\" class=\" wp-image-187903\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-being-awarded-Padma-Bhushan-Award-by-K.-R.-Narayanan-in-2001.jpg\" alt=\"Aroon Purie being awarded Padma Bhushan Award by K. R. Narayanan in 2001\" width=\"302\" height=\"240\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-187903\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aroon Purie being awarded Padma Bhushan Award by K. R. Narayanan in 2001<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2002,\u00a0 Aroon Purie received the Hall of Fame Award from the Advertising Club of Kolkata.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2008, Aroon Purie was conferred with the NT Award for Lifetime Achievement from www.Indiatelevision.com.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In March 2022, he received the ABLF lifetime achievement award for his work in Journalism.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"FactsTrivia\"><\/span>Facts\/Trivia<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>According to Aroon Purie, when the first issue of the India Today magazine dated 1-15 December 1975 was released then he was designated as the person in charge (publisher), and his sister, Madhu Purie, was listed as the editor of the magazine. Aroon mentioned in the magazine that the goal of the magazine was to provide information to the people interested in India who lived outside the country.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_187904\" style=\"width: 397px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Madhu-Trehan-while-interviewing-for-India-Today-Group.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-187904\" class=\" wp-image-187904\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Madhu-Trehan-while-interviewing-for-India-Today-Group.jpg\" alt=\"Madhu Trehan while interviewing for India Today Group\" width=\"387\" height=\"386\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Madhu-Trehan-while-interviewing-for-India-Today-Group.jpg 406w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Madhu-Trehan-while-interviewing-for-India-Today-Group-300x300.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Madhu-Trehan-while-interviewing-for-India-Today-Group-150x150.jpg 150w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Madhu-Trehan-while-interviewing-for-India-Today-Group-65x65.jpg 65w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 387px) 100vw, 387px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-187904\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Madhu Trehan while interviewing for India Today Group<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2022, while delivering a lecture at the Subhas Ghosal Memorial organised by the AAAI (Advertising Agencies Association of India) and the Subhas Ghosal Foundation, in Mumbai, Aroon Purie narrated an important moment that happened in 1980 when the India Today magazine used a method called psephology to predict the results of the general elections. Aroon Purie said,<br \/>\n<blockquote><p>We made the right prediction, and this really made people trust the magazine more.&#8221;<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_187897\" style=\"width: 431px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-while-delivering-the-Subhas-Ghosal-Memorial-Lecture-2022-organised-by-the-AAAI-.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-187897\" class=\" wp-image-187897\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-while-delivering-the-Subhas-Ghosal-Memorial-Lecture-2022-organised-by-the-AAAI-.jpg\" alt=\"Aroon Purie while delivering the Subhas Ghosal Memorial Lecture 2022 organised by the AAAI\" width=\"421\" height=\"426\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-while-delivering-the-Subhas-Ghosal-Memorial-Lecture-2022-organised-by-the-AAAI-.jpg 545w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-while-delivering-the-Subhas-Ghosal-Memorial-Lecture-2022-organised-by-the-AAAI--297x300.jpg 297w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Aroon-Purie-while-delivering-the-Subhas-Ghosal-Memorial-Lecture-2022-organised-by-the-AAAI--65x65.jpg 65w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 421px) 100vw, 421px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-187897\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Aroon Purie while delivering the Subhas Ghosal Memorial Lecture 2022 organised by the AAAI<\/p><\/div><\/blockquote>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div class=\"489bcfb86580b123547338c91db0eff2\" data-index=\"3\" style=\"float: none; margin:3px 0 3px 0; text-align:center;\">\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\r\n     style=\"display:block\"\r\n     data-ad-format=\"autorelaxed\"\r\n     data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-6769524711517462\"\r\n     data-ad-slot=\"2473600074\"><\/ins>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"font-size: 0px; height: 0px; line-height: 0px; margin: 0; padding: 0; clear: both;\"><\/div><div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_label_expand_187706_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">References<\/span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_button_plus_187706_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">[+]<\/span><span><\/span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_button_minus_187706_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button collapsed\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_187706_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">[\u2212]<\/span><\/p><\/div> <div id=\"footnote_references_container_187706_1\" class=\"collapsed\"><table class=\"footnotes_table footnote-reference-container\"><caption class=\"accessibility\">References<\/caption> <tbody> \r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi pointer\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_187706_1_1\" class=\"footnote_backlink\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>1<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.telegraphindia.com\/india\/dame-dilemma-for-doon-president-s-co-ed-suggestion-evokes-mixed-reaction\/cid\/473014\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Telegraph Online<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi pointer\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_187706_1_2\" class=\"footnote_backlink\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>2<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.indiatoday.in\/india\/story\/india-today-group-chairman-aroon-purie-honoured-with-ablf-lifetime-achievement-award-1926185-2022-03-16\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">India Today<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi pointer\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_187706_1_3\" class=\"footnote_backlink\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>3<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.indiatoday.in\/magazine\/editor-s-note\/story\/20180129-from-the-editor-in-chief-hindu-vs-hindutva-aroon-purie-1148708-2018-01-19\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">India Today<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi pointer\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_187706_1_4\" class=\"footnote_backlink\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>4<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.newslaundry.com\/2022\/10\/31\/supreme-court-quashes-defamation-case-against-india-todays-aroon-purie#:~:text=The%20case%20pertains%20to%20a%202007%20report%20in%20the%20magazine.&amp;text=The%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20quashed,in%20the%20magazine%20in%202007\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">News Laundry<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi pointer\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_187706_1_5\" class=\"footnote_backlink\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>5<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/slate.com\/culture\/2010\/10\/my-slatearticle-on-rajinikanth-was-plagiarized-by-india-today.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Slate<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n <\/tbody> <\/table> <\/div><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Aroon Purie is an Indian media tycoon who is the founder-publisher and editor-in-chief of India Today magazine. He used to lead the India Today Group. He is the managing director of Thomson Press (India) Limited and chairman of TV Today. He is the recipient of the Padma Bhushan Award. Aroon Purie is the former editor-in-chief of Reader&#8217;s Digest India. In 2017, he gave control of the India Today Group to his daughter, Kalli Purie. Wiki\/Biography Aroon Purie was born in 1944 (age 74 years; as of 2023) in Lahore, Punjab province, British India. He has completed his school education at <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":41,"featured_media":187772,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[19],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/187706"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/41"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=187706"}],"version-history":[{"count":9,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/187706\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":201666,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/187706\/revisions\/201666"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/187772"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=187706"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=187706"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=187706"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}